'''Alfie Charles Jones''' (born 7 October 1997) is a professional [[Association football|soccer]] player who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] or [[midfielder]] for {{English football updater|Middboro}} club [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]]. Born in England, he plays for the [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada national team]].

==Career==
[[File:Alfie Jones.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Jones with [[Hull City A.F.C.|Hull City]] in 2023]]

Jones grew up in [[Long Ashton]], a small village on the outskirts of [[Bristol]]. He attended [[Birdwell School]] and [[Backwell School]]. He played at the Southampton Academy in Bath.{{citation needed|date=June 2021}}

Jones played on loan for [[Scottish Premiership]] club [[St Mirren F.C.|St Mirren]] during the 2018–19 season, but the agreement was terminated by St Mirren in January 2019.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/46785415 |title=St Mirren; Hearts' Ryan Edwards and Southampton's Alfie Jones have loans cut short |work=BBC Sport |date=7 January 2019 |accessdate=7 January 2019}}</ref>

On 2 July 2019, Jones signed a season-long loan with [[Gillingham F.C.|Gillingham]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gillinghamfootballclub.com/news/2019/july/alfie-jones-signing/|title=Gills sign Alfie Jones on loan|website=www.gillinghamfootballclub.com|date=2 July 2019|accessdate=2 July 2019}}</ref> During his spell with the club, he made 36 appearances in all competitions.<ref>{{cite web|title=Alfie Jones {{!}} Football Stats {{!}} Southampton {{!}} Season 2019/2020 {{!}} Soccer Base|url=https://www.soccerbase.com/players/player.sd?player_id=93986&season_id=152|accessdate=28 June 2020|website=www.soccerbase.com}}</ref>

On 4 September 2020, Jones joined [[EFL League One|League One]] side [[Hull City A.F.C.|Hull City]] for an undisclosed fee, signing a one-year deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hullcitytigers.com/hull-city-sign-alfie-jones/|title=HULL CITY SIGN ALFIE JONES|publisher=[[Hull City A.F.C.]]|date=4 September 2020|accessdate=4 September 2020}}{{dead link|date=August 2023 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> He made his debut for the club on 8 September 2020, in the 
1–2 loss to [[Leicester City F.C. Under-23s and Academy|Leicester City U21]] in the first round match of the [[EFL Trophy]].<ref>{{cite news
  | url = https://www.hullcitytigers.com/matches/fixtures/first-team/202021/september/hull-city-vs-leicester-city-u21-on-08-sep-20/
  | title = Hull City 1–2 Leicester City – EFL Trophy Match Report
  | date = 8 September 2020
  | publisher = Hull City A.F.C.
  | accessdate = 8 September 2020
  | archive-date = 14 May 2021
  | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210514143042/https://www.hullcitytigers.com/matches/fixtures/first-team/202021/september/hull-city-vs-leicester-city-u21-on-08-sep-20/
  | url-status = dead
  }}</ref>
On 18 May 2021, the club announced that they had exercised the option of a one-year contract extension for Jones.<ref>{{cite news
 | url = https://www.hullcitytigers.com/news/2021/may/retained-list-confirmed/
 | title = Retained List Confirmed
 | date = 18 May 2021
